  "description": [
    "Archives Building Still Officially Empty but Records of War Agencies Are Inside Data Stored Under Decree of Wilson Needs Recog nition of Council By LAWRENCE CARTER Officially there isnt a single docu ment in the new 8750000 Archives Building but actually there is being stored there some 17000 cubic feet of records of the wartime Grain Wheat and Food Administrations This fact brings up a fine point of law In 1927 President Coolidge or dered these documents stored away as soon as an archives building was completed But the act of Congress authorizing construction left it up to the National Archives Council as to what documents should be admitted to the vaults These wartime documents had been stored in a garage and it was believed their preservation depended on prompt removal to a safer place The moving began early this week NEED RECOGNITION While these valuable mementos of the Wilson regime are in the Ar chives Building they cannot be re stored and classified until they have been officially recognized by the Council There are 102 persons employed in the Archives Building The majority are secretaries and the remainder are technicians working out a system of classification and surveying the"
